# Cline Rules — RealitkaAI

## Model Routing
- Plan Mode: DeepSeek V3 (planning, architecture, brainstorming)
- Act Mode: Claude Sonnet 4.6 (implementation, coding)

## Context Management
- When context reaches 70%, finish current step and propose new task
- Never read repo-structure file
- Never read package-lock.json
- Read only files directly relevant to current task

## Response Style
- Be concise — no verbose explanations unless asked
- No confirmation of obvious steps
- Code blocks only, no surrounding prose when delivering code

## Task Approach
- Always start complex tasks in Plan Mode first
- Use @ mentions for specific files instead of broad exploration
- Maximum 2 Cline instances running in parallel

## Cost Protection

- Never scan entire repository unless explicitly requested
- Prefer targeted file reads
- Avoid recursive exploration
- Stop and ask before reading more than 10 files
- Use concise responses

## Production Safety Rules

- Never remove existing production functionality
- Never overwrite existing DB tables without migration
- Always generate migrations incrementally
- Never expose secrets in frontend
- Never trust incoming webhook payloads
- Always validate external input
- Never block webhook response with heavy processing
- Prefer defensive coding over concise coding
